        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 4:40AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 440 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Aliceville, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Snoddy, Carrollton, Dillburg, Ralph, George Downer
Airport, Union, Fosters Boat Landing, Mound State Park, Kirk,
Pleasant Ridge, Lewiston, Benevola, Johnston Lake, Echola, Lake
Lurleen State Park, Elrod, Garden, North Pickens Airport, and McShan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for west central
Alabama.</instruction>
